text: Bought 2 kopi o kosong dilo(mean direct pour, no add water) and 1 kopi gao sew dai @ $3.40 only. Coffee is excellent! Thick and smooth. Made with traditional socks bag coffee style. Really is a die for coffee..

This stall is run by a grandmother and her daughter, and is super popular with the neighbourhood - especially for their coffee and tea. There will always be a queue and when it comes to your turn, be sure to be ready with your order, else you will be shouted at.

I'm impressed by their iced teh - the grandma prepares it from scratch and uses a milk frothing machine to froth it before serving it to you. One cup costs $1.30.

This is my to-go every time I visit this hawker centre.
Strong Singapore local kopi. Very popular stall at this hawker center.
Good coffee, especially the ice coffee..
